The following files contain code adapted from the Vercel Workflow SDK e2e test suite:

  e2e-v5/workflows/e2e.ts                — workflow definitions
  e2e-v5/workflows/helpers.ts            — cross-file error helper functions
  e2e-v5/workflows/_imported_step_only.ts — step-only file (no workflow)
  e2e-v5/workflows/98_duplicate_case.ts   — duplicate workflow for ID collision testing
  e2e-v5/workflows/serde-models.ts        — cross-context serialization models
  e2e-v5/workflows/serde-steps.ts         — cross-context serialization steps
  e2e-v5/lib/steps/paths-alias-test.ts    — path alias test helper
  e2e-v5/app/.well-known/agent/v1/steps.ts — .well-known/agent discovery test
  e2e-v5/pages/api/trigger-pages.ts        — Pages Router trigger endpoint
  e2e-v5/test/vercel-e2e.test.ts          — e2e test scenarios (including the
                                         resilient-start and outputStream
                                         getTailIndex/getChunks ports from
                                         packages/core/e2e/e2e.test.ts)
  e2e-v5/test/helper.ts                   — shared test infrastructure

The CBOR queue transport in packages/world/src/lib/{client,queue}.ts follows
the wire contract from @workflow/world-vercel (packages/world-vercel/src/queue.ts):
`application/cbor` content-type, CBOR-first deserialization with JSON fallback.
